      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RUBY CHICKS (4) turned in a fine effort to win by 2 lengths at today's course and distance last start which was an improvement on the first-up run. Tackling an easier race so she is a big chance again. IMPARDOO (3) was in a different class last time, sitting just off the speed before letting down impressively for a 3 length win at Atherton over 1000m. Sure to measure up again. VALENKI (2) finished third last time over 1250m at this track, beaten 5 lengths. Yet to miss the frame in three starts over this course and distance. Has the ability to take care of this field. RED HOT LIZZIE (6) returned from a spell a week ago when she was beaten 17 lengths into eighth over 1000m at Moranbah. Fitter so expect a better run this time.",
